<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="72" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1053,1476]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,321,1053,1079]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Ecology:—</emphasis>
The species was found associated with some woody plants (
<figureCitation box="[975,1072,1053,1079]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1552,1574]" captionTargetBox="[160,1435,201,1521]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[151,1436,190,1528]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sphaeropteris guanxiensis.—A &amp; B. Habit.—C. Petioles and scales on the trunk.—D &amp; E. Petiole crosscutting and the annular vascular bundles (photographed by Jun-Jie Luo).—F, G &amp; H. Spore morphology." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448019" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448019/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Figure 2</figureCitation>
: A, B), such as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sprengel 1826: 878) Muller Argoviensis (1865: 189)" authorityName="Muller Argoviensis" authorityPageNumber="189" authorityYear="1865" baseAuthorityName="Sprengel" baseAuthorityPageNumber="878" baseAuthorityYear="1826" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Mallotus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[1238,1451,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Mallotus japonicus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sprengel, C. P. J." box="[144,366,1089,1115]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" refId="ref2974" refString="Sprengel, C. P. J. (1826) Systema Vegetabilium, edition decimal sexta. Vol. 3. Subntibus Librariae Dieterichianae, Gottingae, 936 pp." type="book" year="1826">Sprengel 1826: 878</bibRefCitation>
) Müller Argoviensis (1865: 189)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus (1753: 200)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityPageNumber="200" authorityYear="1753" box="[751,1197,1089,1116]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Mangifera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis box="[751,946,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Mangifera indica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[953,1197,1089,1116]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" refId="ref2603" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1753) Species plantarum. Vol. 2. Imprensis Laurentii Salvii, Homiae, 1200 pp." type="book" year="1753">Linnaeus (1753: 200)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="McClure (1936: 639)" authorityName="McClure" authorityPageNumber="639" authorityYear="1936" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bambusa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chungii">
<emphasis box="[1256,1451,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Bambusa chungii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="McClure, F. A." box="[136,380,1125,1152]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" pagination="639 - 643" refId="ref2651" refString="McClure, F. A. (1936) The Chinese species of Schizostachyum. Lingnan Science Journal 15: 639 - 643." type="journal article" year="1936">McClure (1936: 639)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It was also found to be associated with species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bercht. &amp; J. Presl" authorityName="Bercht. &amp; J. Presl" box="[962,1292,1125,1152]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Arecaceae Bercht. &amp; J. Presl</taxonomicName>
, ferns such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus (1753: 1079)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityPageNumber="1079" authorityYear="1753" box="[136,594,1161,1188]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="Asplenium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nidus">
<emphasis box="[136,324,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Asplenium nidus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[333,594,1161,1188]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" refId="ref2603" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1753) Species plantarum. Vol. 2. Imprensis Laurentii Salvii, Homiae, 1200 pp." type="book" year="1753">Linnaeus (1753: 1079)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Beddome 1866: 159) Tagawa (1966: 193)" authorityName="Tagawa" authorityPageNumber="193" authorityYear="1966" baseAuthorityName="Beddome" baseAuthorityPageNumber="159" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[608,1398,1161,1188]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Lemmaphyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rostratum">
<emphasis box="[608,898,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Lemmaphyllum rostratum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Beddome, R. H." box="[915,1149,1161,1188]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" refId="ref1949" refString="Beddome, R. H. (1866) The Ferns of British India: being figures and descriptions of ferns from all parts of British India (exclusive of those figured in &quot; The Ferns of Southern India and Ceylon &quot;). Vol. 1. Adelphi Press, Madras, 180 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 63305" type="book" year="1866">Beddome 1866: 159</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Tagawa, M." box="[1166,1398,1161,1188]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" refId="ref3005" refString="Tagawa, M. (1966) Polypodiaceae. In: Hara, H. (Ed.) Flora of Eastern Himalaya. University of Tokyo, Tokyo, 742 pp." type="book" year="1966">Tagawa (1966: 193)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus 1763: 1524) Copeland (1929: 111)" authorityName="Copeland" authorityPageNumber="111" authorityYear="1929" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityPageNumber="1524" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[136,927,1197,1224]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Microsorum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="punctatum">
<emphasis box="[136,401,1198,1223]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Microsorum punctatum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[418,661,1197,1224]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" refId="ref2626" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1763) Species Plantarum, Editio Secunda 2. Imprensis Direct. Laurentii Salvii, Holmiae, 1864 pp." type="book" year="1763">Linnaeus 1763: 1524</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Copeland, E. B." box="[679,927,1197,1223]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" pagination="45 - 128" refId="ref2323" refString="Copeland, E. B. (1929) The oriental genera of Polypodiaceae. University of California Publications in Botany 16: 45 - 128." type="journal article" year="1929">Copeland (1929: 111)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
were found to be associated with their trunk. Approximately 
<specimenCount box="[313,404,1233,1260]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" type="adult">50 adult</specimenCount>
plants and a few young ones were found in the population.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1053,1476]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3341587301" collectionCode="IUCN, EN" country="China" county="Endangered" location="Local" municipality="The" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Guangxi">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,527,1269,1295]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
<collectionCode box="[189,261,1269,1295]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">IUCN</collectionCode>
Red List category:—
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[528,841,1269,1295]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Cyatheaceae" genus="Sphaeropteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cyatheales" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="guangxiensis">
<emphasis box="[528,841,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Sphaeropteris guangxiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a restricted geographic distribution, and yet not found in other regions out of the 
<typeStatus box="[519,567,1306,1332]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">type</typeStatus>
locality. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03A0CD0F3D751A561FBFFF6F5212358A:8ED62AC23D771A561D94FA8255CD357D" box="[675,739,1305,1331]" country="China" county="Endangered" municipality="The" name="Local" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" stateProvince="Guangxi">Local</location>
people occasionally utilize this species as firewood. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03A0CD0F3D751A561FBFFF6F5212358A:8ED62AC23D771A561A73FA82525E357D" box="[1348,1392,1305,1331]" country="China" county="Endangered" municipality="The" name="Our" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" stateProvince="Guangxi">Our</location>
field investigations showed that there were no abnormalities in the spores of the new species which indicated that the new species can replenish themselves. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03A0CD0F3D751A561FBFFF6F5212358A:8ED62AC23D771A561D3AFAF955533532" box="[525,637,1378,1404]" country="China" county="Endangered" municipality="The" name="Moreover" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" stateProvince="Guangxi">Moreover</location>
, we observed hundreds individuals of this species in a large population at the border of 
<collectingRegion box="[315,520,1413,1439]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Guangxi Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[532,599,1413,1439]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[653,752,1413,1439]" name="Vietnam" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingMunicipality box="[761,805,1413,1439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">The</collectingMunicipality>
status of the new species can be classified as 
<collectingCounty box="[1318,1452,1413,1439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Endangered</collectingCounty>
(
<collectionCode box="[144,184,1449,1475]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">EN</collectionCode>
)
</materialsCitation>
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3341587302" box="[199,263,1449,1475]" collectionCode="EN" country="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" specimenCode="A2" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Guangxi">
[
<specimenCode box="[206,244,1449,1475]" collectionCode="A" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" type="Herbarium">A2</specimenCode>
a;
</materialsCitation>
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3341587303" box="[270,1336,1449,1476]" collectionCode="B" country="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" specimenCode="B2" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Guangxi">
<specimenCode box="[270,304,1449,1476]" collectionCode="B" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15534" name="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Zentraleinrichtung der Freien Universitaet" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" type="Herbarium">B2</specimenCode>
